race.comment: FIRE THE GUARD (1) disappointed last start at Kalgoorlie but was in much better form prior to that performance. Given a freshen since that run and this looks a very suitable race from a good draw. Can bounce back to his best and notch up his third win. UNDERCOVER SNIPER (2) ran well despite being friendless in betting when resuming last time over 1103m at this track, finishing third and beaten 1.5 lengths at $26. Commendable record at this trip with a win and three minor placings and is expected to be in the finish. BE MY BELLE (10) didn't make an impact at her last run before going for a spell, finishing 12th and beaten 13 lengths over 1400m at Belmont. Lines up for the new trainer on her home track now. Can be an improver on resumption. LIVE LUCKY (6) lines up for the first time since February 6. Looking to emulate her win at this track to kick off the last campaign. Can make her presence felt.
